            [
                'id' => 473,
                'code' => "PD9911",
                'name' => "Child Developmental Assessment",
                'definition' => "Describes whether the organization has screened children who are using the organization's products/services for developmental progress and delays as of the end of the reporting period.",
                'calculation' => null,
                'usage_guidance' => "This metric is intended to capture whether the organization has screened the children it serves for developmental progress. \n\nDevelopmental screening includes screening for learning disabilities, speech or language problems, autism, intellectual disability, emotional or behavioral conditions, hearing or vision impairment, and attention deficit/hyperactivity disorder (ADHD).\n\nTo measure how many children are developmentally on track, organizations are encouraged to use Client Individuals: Total (PI4060) disaggregated by Developmental Status (PI0045).",
