                'definition' => "Number of status-quo products that were replaced by products sold during the reporting period.",
                'calculation' => null,
                'usage_guidance' => "This metric is intended to capture the number of existing products replaced by products the organization sold during the reporting period. Organizations should select and report a single product type replaced. For example, for a solar lantern, organizations may report the product replaced as kerosene, lanterns, candles, battery torches, or generators.\n\nThis metric may be estimated from a representative sample.\n\nWhen calculating the number of products replaced, organizations should consider the operating life of the replacement product. For example, a solar lantern, over its operating life, may replace hundreds of kerosene lanterns.",
